# 20. Troubleshooting Runbooks (SRE)

## High CPU Usage

Symptoms:

* system slow
* high load average

Check load:

```
uptime
```

Identify processes consuming CPU:

```
top
```

or

```
ps aux --sort=-%cpu | head
```

Kill problematic process:

```
kill -15 PID
kill -9 PID
```

---

## Disk Full

Check disk usage:

```
df -h
```

Find large directories:

```
du -sh /*
```

Check deleted files still open:

```
lsof | grep deleted
```

Restart service using deleted file.

---

## Memory Leak

Check memory usage:

```
free -m
```

Find top memory consumers:

```
ps aux --sort=-%mem | head
```

Check OOM killer logs:

```
dmesg | grep -i kill
```

---

## Process Hanging

Check processes:

```
ps -ef
```

Check process status:

```
ps aux
```

Kill stuck process:

```
kill PID
kill -9 PID
```

---

## Service Not Starting

Check service status:

```
systemctl status service_name
```

View logs:

```
journalctl -u service_name
```

Restart service:

```
systemctl restart service_name
```

---

## Port Already in Use

Find process using port:

```
lsof -i :80
```

or

```
netstat -tulpn
```

Kill process if needed.

---

